[39m  @clawsweeper Re: docs line 95 / "missing required [38;5;189m`--provider`[39m flag" — [38;5;189m`tts[39m
  [38;5;189mconvert`[39m does not have a [38;5;189m`--provider`[39m flag. The CLI selects the provider
  through [38;5;189m`--model <provider>/<model>`[39m, as defined in [38;5;189m`src/cli/capability-[39m
  [38;5;189mcli.ts:1994-2003`[39m (the only options are [38;5;189m`--text/--channel/--voice/--model/--[39m
  [38;5;189moutput/--local/--gateway/--json`[39m). The docs example [38;5;189m`--model[39m
  [38;5;189msenseaudio/senseaudio-tts-1.5-260319`[39m is the correct invocation form. The
  sibling [38;5;189m`tts voices`[39m and [38;5;189m`tts providers`[39m subcommands do accept [38;5;189m`--provider`[39m,
  but [38;5;189m`tts convert`[39m does not.

